cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on improving navigation instructions for users, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of computer vision to select global landmarks suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study conducted to demonstrate the effectiveness of the system involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and the visualization of navigation routes (cs.GR).
